parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knocking or pinging can lead to premature engine wear, increased oil consumption, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Excessive engine knocking or pinging at high RPM
engine knocking or pinging under load

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause engine overheating, which can result in costly repairs and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Engine using excessive amounts of oil

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Warping of Rotors and Brake Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature warping of rotors and brake pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Vibrations or pulsations when applying the brakes
squealing or grinding noises when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sensor can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to fuel pump failure, which can result in engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping out of gear can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps out of gear while driving
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause serious injury to the driver and passengers, including lacerations and potentially life-threatening harm.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters or explodes suddenly
causing broken glass and debris to fall into the vehicle
and potentially causing injuries to occupants.
